Interface ListToVector

All Superinterfaces:
CustomizableRefactoring<ListToVector>, Refactoring
public sealed interface ListToVector extends CustomizableRefactoring<ListToVector>
This refactoring allows converting vector properties that have been created with either db.create.setNodeVectorProperty or db.create.setRelationshipVectorPropert to the new actual vector property type available in Neo4j 2025.10.

Using any of the above procedures will create entity properties of type LIST<FLOAT NOT NULL> NOT NULL which are not compatible with the VECTOR type. This migration will convert the former into the latter, opening up the data-model for all further improvements for vector indexes and vector searches in Neo4j to come.

Only properties of type LIST<FLOAT NOT NULL> NOT NULL will be matched and converted by default. If this is not what you want, configure a custom query via onNodesMatching(String) or onRelationshipsMatching(String).

All queries will be prefixed with CYPHER 25.

Since:
3.0.0
Author:
Michael J. Simons
